                            <comment id="14568976" author="alanb" created="Wed, 22 Mar 2023 23:41:35 -0700"  >A survey of usages that show real cases where the buf isn&amp;#39;t used would help the discussion, it may be that this issue should be closed as WNF.</comment>
                            <comment id="14568898" author="stsypanov" created="Wed, 22 Mar 2023 13:28:33 -0700"  >Sure, I&amp;#39;m just pointing out, that as soon as read1() often doesn&amp;#39;t do intermediate copying of the bytes into buffer we could skip buffer initialization.</comment>
                            <comment id="14568896" author="alanb" created="Wed, 22 Mar 2023 13:17:23 -0700"  >Any changes here will require care and careful review so we not to break subclasses, close or the Process implementation. Note that BIS does not override readNBytes/readAllBytes at this time so the default implementation will use the existing read methods.</comment>
